SIMPLE: congruous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Congruous
<hw>Con"gru*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>congruus</ets>, fr. <ets>congruere</ets> to come together, to
coincide, to agree. Of uncertain origin.]</ety> <def>Suitable or
concordant; accordant; fit; harmonious; correspondent;
consistent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not <qex>congruous</qex> to the nature of epic poetry.</q>
<rj><qau>Blair.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is no ways <qex>congruous</qex> that God should be always
frightening men into an acknowledgment of the truth.</q>
<rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Congruously</ent>⟦br⟧
